---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  meta={{
    title: 'Terms of Use | StackHunt',
    description:
      'Terms governing access to StackHunt, including permitted use, content limitations, and liability boundaries.',
    canonical: 'https://stackhunt.co/terms',
  }}
>
  <main class="min-h-screen bg-gradient-to-b from-zinc-950 to-zinc-900">
    <div class="border-b border-zinc-800 bg-zinc-950/50 backdrop-blur-sm">
      <div class="container mx-auto max-w-5xl px-4 py-8">
        <nav class="mb-4 flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-zinc-500">
          <a href="/" class="hover:text-indigo-400 transition">Home</a>
          <span>/</span>
          <span class="text-zinc-400">Terms</span>
        </nav>

        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-zinc-100 mb-3">Terms of Use</h1>
        <p class="text-lg text-zinc-400">
          These terms govern your access to StackHunt. By using this site, you agree to them.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="container mx-auto max-w-5xl px-4 py-12">
      <article
        class="prose prose-invert max-w-none prose-headings:text-zinc-100 prose-p:text-zinc-400 prose-strong:text-zinc-200 prose-li:text-zinc-400 prose-h2:border-b prose-h2:border-zinc-800 prose-h2:pb-3 prose-h2:mb-6"
      >
        <h2>1. Service Scope</h2>
        <p>
          StackHunt provides editorial intelligence reports about software tools. Content is for
          informational purposes and does not constitute legal, tax, investment, or procurement advice.
        </p>

        <h2>2. Content Nature</h2>
        <p>
          StackHunt content combines factual references and editorial analysis. Some sections include
          subjective interpretation. You are responsible for validating material business decisions directly
          with vendors.
        </p>

        <h2>3. Permitted Use</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>You may browse, compare, and reference StackHunt pages for internal decision support.</li>
          <li>You may not impersonate StackHunt, misrepresent our content, or use it for unlawful activity.</li>
          <li>You may not systematically copy, republish, or resell substantial portions of StackHunt output.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>4. Accuracy and Freshness</h2>
        <p>
          We use quality controls and source attribution, but software products change quickly. We do not
          guarantee that every detail remains current at all times.
        </p>

        <h2>5. Affiliate Relationships</h2>
        <p>
          Some outbound links may be affiliate links. This does not change your purchase price. See our
          <a href="/disclosure">Disclosure page</a> for details.
        </p>

        <h2>6. Liability Limits</h2>
        <p>
          To the maximum extent permitted by law, StackHunt is not liable for indirect, incidental, special,
          consequential, or punitive damages arising from use of the site. Your use is at your own risk.
        </p>

        <h2>7. Changes</h2>
        <p>
          We may update these terms as the product evolves. Continued use after updates means you accept the
          revised terms.
        </p>

        <h2>8. Contact</h2>
        <p>
          Questions about these terms can be sent through our corrections/contact channels linked on the site.
        </p>

        <p class="text-sm text-zinc-500">
          Last updated: {
            new Date().toLocaleDateString('en-US', {
              month: 'long',
              day: 'numeric',
              year: 'numeric',
            })
          }
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
